{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783912467379,"sessionID":"ses_0a68bc60effeJzWL51JC6bkniv","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_L3DUeW80kSNgY70t8Jf8A6RN","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/asset_template.md","offset":1,"limit":500},"error":"File not found: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/asset_template.md\n\nDid you mean one of these?\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/skill_asset_template.md","time":{"start":1783912467369,"end":1783912467375}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09bbfd2e8cf10090016a5458131a648191a6828158e6aad9b7"}},"id":"prt_f59780ba6001AW45F6hqaM9bl1","sessionID":"ses_0a68bc60effeJzWL51JC6bkniv","messageID":"msg_f59777c8b001R4striWjqU0bS1"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783912467379,"sessionID":"ses_0a68bc60effeJzWL51JC6bkniv","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_aBn6c22Cjii19yshQkVRsP2c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/assets/code_quality_checklist/overview_header_and_comments.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/assets/code_quality_checklist/overview_header_and_comments.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Code Quality Checklist\n3: description: Validation checklist for JavaScript and CSS code quality and style compliance.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"webflow code quality checklist\"\n6:   - \"javascript css style compliance\"\n7:   - \"file header checks webflow\"\n8:   - \"review baseline handoff\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: version: 3.5.0.17\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Code Quality Checklist\n15: \n16: Validation checklist for JavaScript and CSS code quality and style compliance.\n17: \n18: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n19: \n20: ### Purpose\n21: \n22: Validate code against style standards before claiming implementation is complete. This checklist ensures consistent, maintainable code across the codebase.\n23: \n24: ### Usage\n25: \n26: 1. **Load** this checklist when completing code implementation\n27: 2. **Identify** file type (JavaScript → Sections 2-7, CSS → Section 8)\n28: 3. **Validate** each applicable item against the code\n29: 4. **Mark** items `[x]` when verified\n30: 5. **Block** completion if any P0 item fails\n31: 6. **Document** P2 deferrals with reasons\n32: \n33: ### Language Coverage\n34: \n35: | Language | File Extension | Checklist Sections |\n36: |----------|----------------|-------------------|\n37: | JavaScript | `.js` | Sections 2-7 |\n38: | CSS | `.css` | Section 8 |\n39: \n40: ### Review Baseline Handoff\n41: \n42: For formal findings-first review output, run `sk-code`'s code-review mode as the baseline and use this checklist as the web overlay.\n43: \n44: - Severity model and review output contract: `sk-code/code-review/references/quick_reference.md`\n45: - Baseline security/quality/test review checks: `sk-code`'s code-review mode references\n46: - This checklist: web-specific JavaScript/CSS standards evidence\n47: \n48: ### Source Standards (per-language tree)\n49: \n50: - [shared/cross_language_rules.md](../../../code-webflow/references/shared/cross_language_rules.md) - Cross-language rules (file naming, comment WHY-not-WHAT, banner format, platform prefixes)\n51: - [javascript/style_guide.md](../../../code-webflow/references/javascript/style_guide/overview_naming_and_structure.md) - JS naming (`snake_case`), file structure, formatting, JSDoc, debug logging\n52: - [javascript/quality_standards.md](../../../code-webflow/references/javascript/quality_standards/init_dom_error_and_async.md) - JS defensive patterns + JS naming/init enforcement\n53: - [css/style_guide.md](../../../code-webflow/references/css/style_guide.md) - CSS naming (BEM), custom properties, attribute selectors, animation CSS, file org\n54: - [css/quality_standards.md](../../../code-webflow/references/css/quality_standards/patterns_and_naming_enforcement.md) - CSS quality patterns + CSS enforcement subsections\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## 2. FILE HEADER CHECKS\n59: \n60: **Applies to:** JavaScript (`.js`)\n61: \n62: **Reference:** [code_style_guide.md Section 3](../../../code-webflow/references/javascript/style_guide/overview_naming_and_structure.md)\n63: \n64: ### File Header Format\n65: \n66: - [ ] **[P0] CHK-HDR-01**: File starts with three-line header\n67: - [ ] **[P0] CHK-HDR-02**: Header uses box-drawing character `─` (U+2500), not hyphen `-`\n68: - [ ] **[P0] CHK-HDR-03**: Header line width is 67 characters\n69: - [ ] **[P1] CHK-HDR-04**: Category label is ALL CAPS\n70: - [ ] **[P1] CHK-HDR-05**: Component name is descriptive (2-4 words)\n71: - [ ] **[P2] CHK-HDR-06**: No metadata (dates, authors, version numbers) in header\n72: - [ ] **[P1] CHK-CMT-01**: No ephemeral artifact ids in any comment (ticket/ClickUp ids, spec/phase/packet numbers, ADR ids) — keep the WHY; see [references/universal/code_style_guide.md](../../../shared/references/universal/code_style_guide.md) §4\n73: \n74: **Compliant Example:**\n75: ```javascript\n76: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n77: // VIDEO: BACKGROUND HLS HOVER\n78: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n79: ```\n80: \n81: **Non-Compliant Examples:**\n82: ```javascript\n83: // WRONG: Using hyphens instead of box-drawing characters\n84: // -------------------------------------------------------------------\n85: // VIDEO: BACKGROUND HLS HOVER\n86: // -------------------------------------------------------------------\n87: \n88: // WRONG: Missing header entirely\n89: (() => {\n90:   // code starts without header\n91: })();\n92: \n93: // WRONG: Metadata in header\n94: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n95: // VIDEO: BACKGROUND HLS HOVER - Created 2024-01-15 by Developer\n96: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ## 3. SECTION ORGANIZATION CHECKS\n102: \n103: **Applies to:** JavaScript (`.js`)\n104: \n105: **Reference:** [code_style_guide.md Section 3](../../../code-webflow/references/javascript/style_guide/overview_naming_and_structure.md)\n106: \n107: ### Section Headers\n108: \n109: - [ ] **[P0] CHK-SEC-01**: Code is wrapped in IIFE `(() => { ... })()`\n110: - [ ] **[P0] CHK-SEC-02**: Section headers use multi-line comment format `/* ... */`\n111: - [ ] **[P0] CHK-SEC-03**: Section headers are numbered (1, 2, 3, etc.)\n112: - [ ] **[P1] CHK-SEC-04**: Section titles are ALL CAPS\n113: - [ ] **[P1] CHK-SEC-05**: Section header line width is 68 characters\n114: - [ ] **[P1] CHK-SEC-06**: Opening line starts with `/* ─`\n115: - [ ] **[P1] CHK-SEC-07**: Closing line starts with `──` (not `*/` on same line as title)\n116: \n117: ### Standard Section Order\n118: \n119: - [ ] **[P1] CHK-SEC-08**: Sections follow standard order (when applicable):\n120:   1. CONFIGURATION\n121:   2. UTILITIES\n122:   3. CORE FUNCTIONS\n123:   4. EVENT HANDLERS\n124:   5. INITIALIZE\n125:   6. PUBLIC API (optional)\n126: \n127: - [ ] **[P2] CHK-SEC-09**: Each section contains related code only\n128: \n129: **Compliant Example:**\n130: ```javascript\n131: /* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n132:    1. CONFIGURATION\n133: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n134: const INIT_FLAG = '__componentNameInit';\n135: const INIT_DELAY_MS = 50;\n136: \n137: /* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n138:    2. UTILITIES\n139: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n140: function is_valid(element) { }\n141: ```\n142: \n143: **Non-Compliant Examples:**\n144: ```javascript\n145: // WRONG: Missing numbered sections\n146: /* CONFIGURATION */\n147: const INIT_FLAG = '__componentNameInit';\n148: \n149: // WRONG: Using single-line comments for sections\n150: // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n151: // 1. CONFIGURATION\n152: // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n153: \n154: // WRONG: Title not in ALL CAPS\n155: /* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n156:    1. Configuration\n157: ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n158: ```\n159: \n160: ---\n161: \n162: ## 4. COMMENT QUALITY CHECKS\n163: \n164: **Applies to:** JavaScript (`.js`)\n165: \n166: **Reference:** [code_style_guide.md Section 5](../../../code-webflow/references/javascript/style_guide/overview_naming_and_structure.md)\n167: \n168: ### Comment Principles\n169: \n170: - [ ] **[P0] CHK-CMT-01**: No commented-out code (delete unused code, git preserves history)\n171: - [ ] **[P1] CHK-CMT-02**: Comments explain WHY, not WHAT\n172: - [ ] **[P1] CHK-CMT-03**: Maximum 5 comments per 10 lines of code (not over-commented)\n173: - [ ] **[P1] CHK-CMT-04**: Platform constraints documented (WEBFLOW, MOTION, LENIS, HLS.JS)\n174: \n175: > **Cross-stack motion.dev reference**: For motion.dev API surface, decision matrix, and integration patterns that apply across stacks (not just Webflow), see [`../../../code-webflow/references/animation/quick_start.md`](../../../code-webflow/references/animation/quick_start.md) and the documents in [`../../code-webflow/references/animation`](../../code-webflow/references/animation). The MOTION constraint above remains a Webflow-CDN-specific platform marker.\n176: \n177: ### Function Comments\n178: \n179: - [ ] **[P1] CHK-CMT-05**: Functions have single-line purpose comment above\n180: - [ ] **[P2] CHK-CMT-06**: Complex/public functions have JSDoc with `@param` and `@returns`\n181: \n182: **Compliant Comments (WHY):**\n183: ```javascript\n184: // Prevent background scroll while modal is open\n185: if (window.lenis) {\n186:   window.lenis.stop();\n187: }\n188: \n189: // WEBFLOW: Page transitions may re-execute scripts\n190: if (window[INIT_FLAG]) return;\n191: \n192: // Add 10 second timeout to prevent infinite hang\n193: const timeout = new Promise((_, reject) =>\n194:   setTimeout(() => reject(new Error('Timeout')), 10000)\n195: );\n196: ```\n197: \n198: **Non-Compliant Comments (WHAT):**\n199: ```javascript\n200: // WRONG: Narrates implementation\n201: // Set price to price times 100\n202: const price_cents = price * 100;\n203: \n204: // WRONG: States the obvious\n205: // Loop through items\n206: for (const item of items) { }\n207: \n208: // WRONG: Describes what code does, not why\n209: // Check if element exists\n210: if (element) { }\n211: ```\n212: \n213: ---\n\n(End of file - total 213 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Code Quality Checklist\ndescription: Validation checklist for JavaScript and CSS code quality and style compliance.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"webflow code quality checklist\"\n  - \"javascript css style compliance\"\n  - \"file header checks webflow\"\n  - \"review baseline handoff\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 3.5.0.17\n---\n\n# Code Quality Checklist\n\nValidation checklist for JavaScript and CSS code quality and style compliance.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/assets/code_quality_checklist/overview_header_and_comments.md","text":"---\ntitle: Code Quality Checklist\ndescription: Validation checklist for JavaScript and CSS code quality and style compliance.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"webflow code quality checklist\"\n  - \"javascript css style compliance\"\n  - \"file header checks webflow\"\n  - \"review baseline handoff\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 3.5.0.17\n---\n\n# Code Quality Checklist\n\nValidation checklist for JavaScript and CSS code quality and style compliance.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nValidate code against style standards before claiming implementation is complete. This checklist ensures consistent, maintainable code across the codebase.\n\n### Usage\n\n1. **Load** this checklist when completing code implementation\n2. **Identify** file type (JavaScript → Sections 2-7, CSS → Section 8)\n3. **Validate** each applicable item against the code\n4. **Mark** items `[x]` when verified\n5. **Block** completion if any P0 item fails\n6. **Document** P2 deferrals with reasons\n\n### Language Coverage\n\n| Language | File Extension | Checklist Sections |\n|----------|----------------|-------------------|\n| JavaScript | `.js` | Sections 2-7 |\n| CSS | `.css` | Section 8 |\n\n### Review Baseline Handoff\n\nFor formal findings-first review output, run `sk-code`'s code-review mode as the baseline and use this checklist as the web overlay.\n\n- Severity model and review output contract: `sk-code/code-review/references/quick_reference.md`\n- Baseline security/quality/test review checks: `sk-code`'s code-review mode references\n- This checklist: web-specific JavaScript/CSS standards evidence\n\n### Source Standards (per-language tree)\n\n- [shared/cross_language_rules.md](../../../code-webflow/references/shared/cross_language_rules.md) - Cross-language rules (file naming, comment WHY-not-WHAT, banner format, platform prefixes)\n- [javascript/style_guide.md](../../../code-webflow/references/javascript/style_guide/overview_naming_and_structure.md) - JS naming (`snake_case`), file structure, formatting, JSDoc, debug logging\n- [javascript/quality_standards.md](../../../code-webflow/references/javascript/quality_standards/init_dom_error_and_async.md) - JS defensive patterns + JS naming/init enforcement\n- [css/style_guide.md](../../../code-webflow/references/css/style_guide.md) - CSS naming (BEM), custom properties, attribute selectors, animation CSS, file org\n- [css/quality_standards.md](../../../code-webflow/references/css/quality_standards/patterns_and_naming_enforcement.md) - CSS quality patterns + CSS enforcement subsections\n\n---\n\n## 2. FILE HEADER CHECKS\n\n**Applies to:** JavaScript (`.js`)\n\n**Reference:** [code_style_guide.md Section 3](../../../code-webflow/references/javascript/style_guide/overview_naming_and_structure.md)\n\n### File Header Format\n\n- [ ] **[P0] CHK-HDR-01**: File starts with three-line header\n- [ ] **[P0] CHK-HDR-02**: Header uses box-drawing character `─` (U+2500), not hyphen `-`\n- [ ] **[P0] CHK-HDR-03**: Header line width is 67 characters\n- [ ] **[P1] CHK-HDR-04**: Category label is ALL CAPS\n- [ ] **[P1] CHK-HDR-05**: Component name is descriptive (2-4 words)\n- [ ] **[P2] CHK-HDR-06**: No metadata (dates, authors, version numbers) in header\n- [ ] **[P1] CHK-CMT-01**: No ephemeral artifact ids in any comment (ticket/ClickUp ids, spec/phase/packet numbers, ADR ids) — keep the WHY; see [references/universal/code_style_guide.md](../../../shared/references/universal/code_style_guide.md) §4\n\n**Compliant Example:**\n```javascript\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// VIDEO: BACKGROUND HLS HOVER\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n```\n\n**Non-Compliant Examples:**\n```javascript\n// WRONG: Using hyphens instead of box-drawing characters\n// -------------------------------------------------------------------\n// VIDEO: BACKGROUND HLS HOVER\n// -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n// WRONG: Missing header entirely\n(() => {\n  // code starts without header\n})();\n\n// WRONG: Metadata in header\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// VIDEO: BACKGROUND HLS HOVER - Created 2024-01-15 by Developer\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. SECTION ORGANIZATION CHECKS\n\n**Applies to:** JavaScript (`.js`)\n\n**Reference:** [code_style_guide.md Section 3](../../../code-webflow/references/javascript/style_guide/overview_naming_and_structure.md)\n\n### Section Headers\n\n- [ ] **[P0] CHK-SEC-01**: Code is wrapped in IIFE `(() => { ... })()`\n- [ ] **[P0] CHK-SEC-02**: Section headers use multi-line comment format `/* ... */`\n- [ ] **[P0] CHK-SEC-03**: Section headers are numbered (1, 2, 3, etc.)\n- [ ] **[P1] CHK-SEC-04**: Section titles are ALL CAPS\n- [ ] **[P1] CHK-SEC-05**: Section header line width is 68 characters\n- [ ] **[P1] CHK-SEC-06**: Opening line starts with `/* ─`\n- [ ] **[P1] CHK-SEC-07**: Closing line starts with `──` (not `*/` on same line as title)\n\n### Standard Section Order\n\n- [ ] **[P1] CHK-SEC-08**: Sections follow standard order (when applicable):\n  1. CONFIGURATION\n  2. UTILITIES\n  3. CORE FUNCTIONS\n  4. EVENT HANDLERS\n  5. INITIALIZE\n  6. PUBLIC API (optional)\n\n- [ ] **[P2] CHK-SEC-09**: Each section contains related code only\n\n**Compliant Example:**\n```javascript\n/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   1. CONFIGURATION\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\nconst INIT_FLAG = '__componentNameInit';\nconst INIT_DELAY_MS = 50;\n\n/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   2. UTILITIES\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\nfunction is_valid(element) { }\n```\n\n**Non-Compliant Examples:**\n```javascript\n// WRONG: Missing numbered sections\n/* CONFIGURATION */\nconst INIT_FLAG = '__componentNameInit';\n\n// WRONG: Using single-line comments for sections\n// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n// 1. CONFIGURATION\n// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n// WRONG: Title not in ALL CAPS\n/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   1. Configuration\n──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. COMMENT QUALITY CHECKS\n\n**Applies to:** JavaScript (`.js`)\n\n**Reference:** [code_style_guide.md Section 5](../../../code-webflow/references/javascript/style_guide/overview_naming_and_structure.md)\n\n### Comment Principles\n\n- [ ] **[P0] CHK-CMT-01**: No commented-out code (delete unused code, git preserves history)\n- [ ] **[P1] CHK-CMT-02**: Comments explain WHY, not WHAT\n- [ ] **[P1] CHK-CMT-03**: Maximum 5 comments per 10 lines of code (not over-commented)\n- [ ] **[P1] CHK-CMT-04**: Platform constraints documented (WEBFLOW, MOTION, LENIS, HLS.JS)\n\n> **Cross-stack motion.dev reference**: For motion.dev API surface, decision matrix, and integration patterns that apply across stacks (not just Webflow), see [`../../../code-webflow/references/animation/quick_start.md`](../../../code-webflow/references/animation/quick_start.md) and the documents in [`../../code-webflow/references/animation`](../../code-webflow/references/animation). The MOTION constraint above remains a Webflow-CDN-specific platform marker.\n\n### Function Comments\n\n- [ ] **[P1] CHK-CMT-05**: Functions have single-line purpose comment above\n- [ ] **[P2] CHK-CMT-06**: Complex/public functions have JSDoc with `@param` and `@returns`\n\n**Compliant Comments (WHY):**\n```javascript\n// Prevent background scroll while modal is open\nif (window.lenis) {\n  window.lenis.stop();\n}\n\n// WEBFLOW: Page transitions may re-execute scripts\nif (window[INIT_FLAG]) return;\n\n// Add 10 second timeout to prevent infinite hang\nconst timeout = new Promise((_, reject) =>\n  setTimeout(() => reject(new Error('Timeout')), 10000)\n);\n```\n\n**Non-Compliant Comments (WHAT):**\n```javascript\n// WRONG: Narrates implementation\n// Set price to price times 100\nconst price_cents = price * 100;\n\n// WRONG: States the obvious\n// Loop through items\nfor (const item of items) { }\n\n// WRONG: Describes what code does, not why\n// Check if element exists\nif (element) { }\n```\n\n---","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":213,"totalLines":213,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/assets/code_quality_checklist/overview_header_and_comments.md","time":{"start":1783912467374,"end":1783912467378}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09bbfd2e8cf10090016a5458131a748191b6ca8294d32b02b8"}},"id":"prt_f59780bac00179BJRgcB3y83WP","sessionID":"ses_0a68bc60effeJzWL51JC6bkniv","messageID":"msg_f59777c8b001R4striWjqU0bS1"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783912467387,"sessionID":"ses_0a68bc60effeJzWL51JC6bkniv","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_lL10zlfOjoQ8SGX1off1jzqd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/rust/style_guide/naming_conventions.md","offset":1,"limit":180},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/rust/style_guide/naming_conventions.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Naming Conventions\n3: description: Formatting standards, naming conventions, and TypeScript interoperability rules for Rust files in the OpenCode development environment. — Naming Conventions.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"naming conventions\"\n6:   - \"rust naming conventions\"\n7:   - \"rust style guidance\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: implementation\n10: version: 1.0.0.0\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Naming Conventions\n14: \n15: Formatting standards, naming conventions, and TypeScript interoperability rules for Rust files in the OpenCode development environment.\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: ### Purpose\n22: \n23: Provides focused Rust guidance for naming conventions in the OpenCode development environment.\n24: \n25: ### When to Use\n26: \n27: - Implementing or reviewing Rust code covered by this topic\n28: - Preserving TypeScript interoperability and deterministic behavior\n29: - Applying the corresponding Rust standards at an implementation boundary\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 2. NAMING CONVENTIONS\n34: \n35: ### Types and Traits\n36: \n37: **Style**: `UpperCamelCase`\n38: \n39: ```rust\n40: struct SearchResult {\n41:     score: f64,\n42: }\n43: \n44: enum MemoryState {\n45:     Active,\n46:     Archived,\n47: }\n48: \n49: trait EmbeddingProvider {\n50:     fn embed(&self, input: &str) -> Result<Vec<f32>, EmbedError>;\n51: }\n52: \n53: #[derive(Debug)]\n54: struct EmbedError;\n55: ```\n56: \n57: Treat acronyms as words:\n58: \n59: ```rust\n60: struct UuidParser;\n61: struct HttpClient;\n62: struct WasmAdapter;\n63: struct NapiErrorMapper;\n64: ```\n65: \n66: Do not use `UUIDParser`, `HTTPClient`, or `WASMAdapter`.\n67: \n68: ### Functions, Methods, Variables, and Modules\n69: \n70: **Style**: `snake_case`\n71: \n72: ```rust\n73: mod score_normalization;\n74: \n75: fn calculate_decay_score(age_seconds: u64) -> f64 {\n76:     1.0 / (1.0 + age_seconds as f64)\n77: }\n78: \n79: let search_results = Vec::<String>::new();\n80: let should_retry = false;\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ### Constants and Statics\n84: \n85: **Style**: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`\n86: \n87: ```rust\n88: const MAX_QUERY_LENGTH: usize = 10_000;\n89: const SCORE_SCALE: f64 = 1_000_000.0;\n90: static SUPPORTED_TARGETS: &[&str] = &[\"native\", \"wasm\"];\n91: ```\n92: \n93: A local immutable binding remains `snake_case`; not every `let` binding is a constant.\n94: \n95: ### Generic Parameters\n96: \n97: Use short uppercase names for familiar generic roles and descriptive `UpperCamelCase` names when multiple parameters would otherwise be ambiguous.\n98: \n99: ```rust\n100: fn identity<T>(value: T) -> T {\n101:     value\n102: }\n103: \n104: fn transform<Input, Output, Error>(\n105:     input: Input,\n106:     operation: impl FnOnce(Input) -> Result<Output, Error>,\n107: ) -> Result<Output, Error> {\n108:     operation(input)\n109: }\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ### Getter Names\n113: \n114: Omit `get_` for ordinary, side-effect-free accessors.\n115: \n116: ```rust\n117: struct Candidate {\n118:     id: String,\n119:     score: f64,\n120: }\n121: \n122: impl Candidate {\n123:     fn id(&self) -> &str {\n124:         &self.id\n125:     }\n126: \n127:     fn score(&self) -> f64 {\n128:         self.score\n129:     }\n130: }\n131: ```\n132: \n133: Use a verb when the operation performs work, I/O, mutation, or validation:\n134: \n135: ```rust\n136: fn load_config() -> Result<String, std::io::Error> {\n137:     std::fs::read_to_string(\"config.json\")\n138: }\n139: \n140: fn validate_score(value: f64) -> Result<f64, &'static str> {\n141:     value.is_finite().then_some(value).ok_or(\"score must be finite\")\n142: }\n143: ```\n144: \n145: ### Conversion Method Prefixes\n146: \n147: | Prefix | Meaning | Example |\n148: |--------|---------|---------|\n149: | `as_` | Cheap borrowed view | `as_str()` |\n150: | `to_` | Work or allocation | `to_canonical_json()` |\n151: | `into_` | Consumes `self` | `into_inner()` |\n152: \n153: ```rust\n154: #[derive(Debug, Clone)]\n155: struct SymbolId(String);\n156: \n157: impl SymbolId {\n158:     fn as_str(&self) -> &str {\n159:         &self.0\n160:     }\n161: \n162:     fn to_lowercase_hex(&self) -> String {\n163:         self.0.to_ascii_lowercase()\n164:     }\n165: \n166:     fn into_inner(self) -> String {\n167:         self.0\n168:     }\n169: }\n170: ```\n171: \n172: Do not name an allocating clone `as_bytes_owned`; use `to_bytes`. Do not name a borrowed view `to_str`; use `as_str`.\n173: \n174: ### Newtypes\n175: \n176: Use private-field newtypes for validated or parity-sensitive primitives.\n177: \n178: ```rust\n179: #[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, PartialOrd, Ord, Hash)]\n180: pub struct SymbolId(String);\n\n(Showing lines 1-180 of 324. Use offset=181 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Naming Conventions\ndescription: Formatting standards, naming conventions, and TypeScript interoperability rules for Rust files in the OpenCode development environment. — Naming Conventions.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"naming conventions\"\n  - \"rust naming conventions\"\n  - \"rust style guidance\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.0.0.0\n---\n\n# Naming Conventions\n\nFormatting standards, naming conventions, and TypeScript interoperability rules for Rust files in the OpenCode development environment.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/rust/style_guide/naming_conventions.md","text":"---\ntitle: Naming Conventions\ndescription: Formatting standards, naming conventions, and TypeScript interoperability rules for Rust files in the OpenCode development environment. — Naming Conventions.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"naming conventions\"\n  - \"rust naming conventions\"\n  - \"rust style guidance\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.0.0.0\n---\n\n# Naming Conventions\n\nFormatting standards, naming conventions, and TypeScript interoperability rules for Rust files in the OpenCode development environment.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nProvides focused Rust guidance for naming conventions in the OpenCode development environment.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Implementing or reviewing Rust code covered by this topic\n- Preserving TypeScript interoperability and deterministic behavior\n- Applying the corresponding Rust standards at an implementation boundary\n\n---\n\n## 2. NAMING CONVENTIONS\n\n### Types and Traits\n\n**Style**: `UpperCamelCase`\n\n```rust\nstruct SearchResult {\n    score: f64,\n}\n\nenum MemoryState {\n    Active,\n    Archived,\n}\n\ntrait EmbeddingProvider {\n    fn embed(&self, input: &str) -> Result<Vec<f32>, EmbedError>;\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug)]\nstruct EmbedError;\n```\n\nTreat acronyms as words:\n\n```rust\nstruct UuidParser;\nstruct HttpClient;\nstruct WasmAdapter;\nstruct NapiErrorMapper;\n```\n\nDo not use `UUIDParser`, `HTTPClient`, or `WASMAdapter`.\n\n### Functions, Methods, Variables, and Modules\n\n**Style**: `snake_case`\n\n```rust\nmod score_normalization;\n\nfn calculate_decay_score(age_seconds: u64) -> f64 {\n    1.0 / (1.0 + age_seconds as f64)\n}\n\nlet search_results = Vec::<String>::new();\nlet should_retry = false;\n```\n\n### Constants and Statics\n\n**Style**: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`\n\n```rust\nconst MAX_QUERY_LENGTH: usize = 10_000;\nconst SCORE_SCALE: f64 = 1_000_000.0;\nstatic SUPPORTED_TARGETS: &[&str] = &[\"native\", \"wasm\"];\n```\n\nA local immutable binding remains `snake_case`; not every `let` binding is a constant.\n\n### Generic Parameters\n\nUse short uppercase names for familiar generic roles and descriptive `UpperCamelCase` names when multiple parameters would otherwise be ambiguous.\n\n```rust\nfn identity<T>(value: T) -> T {\n    value\n}\n\nfn transform<Input, Output, Error>(\n    input: Input,\n    operation: impl FnOnce(Input) -> Result<Output, Error>,\n) -> Result<Output, Error> {\n    operation(input)\n}\n```\n\n### Getter Names\n\nOmit `get_` for ordinary, side-effect-free accessors.\n\n```rust\nstruct Candidate {\n    id: String,\n    score: f64,\n}\n\nimpl Candidate {\n    fn id(&self) -> &str {\n        &self.id\n    }\n\n    fn score(&self) -> f64 {\n        self.score\n    }\n}\n```\n\nUse a verb when the operation performs work, I/O, mutation, or validation:\n\n```rust\nfn load_config() -> Result<String, std::io::Error> {\n    std::fs::read_to_string(\"config.json\")\n}\n\nfn validate_score(value: f64) -> Result<f64, &'static str> {\n    value.is_finite().then_some(value).ok_or(\"score must be finite\")\n}\n```\n\n### Conversion Method Prefixes\n\n| Prefix | Meaning | Example |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `as_` | Cheap borrowed view | `as_str()` |\n| `to_` | Work or allocation | `to_canonical_json()` |\n| `into_` | Consumes `self` | `into_inner()` |\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\nstruct SymbolId(String);\n\nimpl SymbolId {\n    fn as_str(&self) -> &str {\n        &self.0\n    }\n\n    fn to_lowercase_hex(&self) -> String {\n        self.0.to_ascii_lowercase()\n    }\n\n    fn into_inner(self) -> String {\n        self.0\n    }\n}\n```\n\nDo not name an allocating clone `as_bytes_owned`; use `to_bytes`. Do not name a borrowed view `to_str`; use `as_str`.\n\n### Newtypes\n\nUse private-field newtypes for validated or parity-sensitive primitives.\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, PartialOrd, Ord, Hash)]\npub struct SymbolId(String);","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":180,"totalLines":324,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/rust/style_guide/naming_conventions.md","time":{"start":1783912467370,"end":1783912467384}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09bbfd2e8cf10090016a5458131a688191a1703487b3ed3534"}},"id":"prt_f59780ba9001hbl2O8HmROBIxk","sessionID":"ses_0a68bc60effeJzWL51JC6bkniv","messageID":"msg_f59777c8b001R4striWjqU0bS1"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783912467387,"sessionID":"ses_0a68bc60effeJzWL51JC6bkniv","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_n0hmLW713Bb9yGQmArGjqsyG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/implementation_workflows/validation_minification_and_cdn.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/implementation_workflows/validation_minification_and_cdn.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Defense-in-Depth Validation, Minification & CDN Deployment\n3: description: Three specialized workflows for writing robust frontend code with proper timing, validation, and cache management. — Defense-in-Depth Validation, Minification & CDN Deployment.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"defense in depth\"\n6:   - \"minification cdn deployment\"\n7:   - \"defense in patterns\"\n8:   - \"webflow defense in\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: version: 3.5.0.10\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Defense-in-Depth Validation, Minification & CDN Deployment\n15: \n16: Three specialized workflows for writing robust frontend code with proper timing, validation, and cache management. — Defense-in-Depth Validation, Minification & CDN Deployment.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Three specialized workflows for writing robust frontend code with proper timing, validation, and cache management. — Defense-in-Depth Validation, Minification & CDN Deployment.\n25: \n26: ### When to Use\n27: \n28: Use this reference when implementing or troubleshooting defense-in-depth validation, minification & cdn deployment.\n29: \n30: ---\n31: \n32: ## 2. DEFENSE-IN-DEPTH VALIDATION\n33: \n34: **When to use**: Form handling, API calls, DOM manipulation, user input, third-party data integration\n35: \n36: ### Core Principle\n37: \n38: Validate at EVERY layer data passes through. Make bugs structurally impossible.\n39: \n40: ### The Four Layers\n41: \n42: #### Layer 1: Entry Point Validation\n43: \n44: Reject obviously invalid input at function boundary.\n45: \n46: ```javascript\n47: function init_video(video_element, config) {\n48:   // Layer 1: Entry validation\n49:   if (!video_element) {\n50:     console.error('[Video] Element is required');\n51:     return null;\n52:   }\n53: \n54:   if (!(video_element instanceof HTMLVideoElement)) {\n55:     console.error('[Video] Must be HTMLVideoElement, got:', video_element);\n56:     return null;\n57:   }\n58: \n59:   if (!config || typeof config !== 'object') {\n60:     console.error('[Video] Config must be object, got:', config);\n61:     return null;\n62:   }\n63: \n64:   // Proceed with initialization...\n65: }\n66: ```\n67: \n68: #### Layer 2: Processing Validation\n69: \n70: Ensure data makes sense for this operation.\n71: \n72: ```javascript\n73: function update_video_source(video_element, new_source) {\n74:   // Layer 1: Entry validation\n75:   if (!video_element || !new_source) {\n76:     console.error('[Video] Missing required parameters');\n77:     return false;\n78:   }\n79: \n80:   // Layer 2: Processing validation\n81:   if (typeof new_source !== 'string' || new_source.trim() === '') {\n82:     console.error('[Video] Source must be non-empty string');\n83:     return false;\n84:   }\n85: \n86:   if (!new_source.match(/\\.(mp4|webm|m3u8)$/i)) {\n87:     console.error('[Video] Invalid video format:', new_source);\n88:     return false;\n89:   }\n90: \n91:   // Safe to proceed\n92:   video_element.src = new_source;\n93:   return true;\n94: }\n95: ```\n96: \n97: #### Layer 3: Output Validation\n98: \n99: Verify results before using them.\n100: \n101: ```javascript\n102: async function fetch_user_data(user_id) {\n103:   // Layer 1: Entry validation\n104:   if (!user_id || typeof user_id !== 'string') {\n105:     throw new Error('Valid user_id required');\n106:   }\n107: \n108:   try {\n109:     const response = await fetch(`/api/users/${user_id}`);\n110: \n111:     // Layer 2: Response validation\n112:     if (!response.ok) {\n113:       throw new Error(`API error: ${response.status}`);\n114:     }\n115: \n116:     const data = await response.json();\n117: \n118:     // Layer 3: Output validation\n119:     if (!data || typeof data !== 'object') {\n120:       throw new Error('Invalid response data structure');\n121:     }\n122: \n123:     if (!data.name || !data.email) {\n124:       throw new Error('Required fields missing from response');\n125:     }\n126: \n127:     // Sanitize output before returning\n128:     return {\n129:       id: String(data.id),\n130:       name: String(data.name).trim(),\n131:       email: String(data.email).toLowerCase().trim(),\n132:       avatar: data.avatar || '/default-avatar.png'\n133:     };\n134: \n135:   } catch (error) {\n136:     console.error('[API] User fetch failed:', error);\n137:     // Return safe default\n138:     return null;\n139:   }\n140: }\n141: ```\n142: \n143: #### Layer 4: Safe Access Patterns\n144: \n145: Prevent crashes when accessing nested data.\n146: \n147: ```javascript\n148: // ❌ DANGEROUS: No validation\n149: function display_user_avatar(user) {\n150:   const avatar = user.profile.avatar.url; // Crashes if any property null\n151:   document.querySelector('[avatar]').src = avatar;\n152: }\n153: \n154: // ✅ SAFE: Multiple layers of validation\n155: function display_user_avatar(user) {\n156:   // Layer 1: User object validation\n157:   if (!user || typeof user !== 'object') {\n158:     console.warn('[Avatar] Invalid user object');\n159:     show_default_avatar();\n160:     return;\n161:   }\n162: \n163:   // Layer 2: Profile validation\n164:   if (!user.profile || typeof user.profile !== 'object') {\n165:     console.warn('[Avatar] User has no profile');\n166:     show_default_avatar();\n167:     return;\n168:   }\n169: \n170:   // Layer 3: Avatar validation\n171:   if (!user.profile.avatar || !user.profile.avatar.url) {\n172:     console.warn('[Avatar] User has no avatar URL');\n173:     show_default_avatar();\n174:     return;\n175:   }\n176: \n177:   // Layer 4: DOM element validation\n178:   const avatar_element = document.querySelector('[avatar]');\n179:   if (!avatar_element) {\n180:     console.error('[Avatar] Avatar element not found');\n181:     return;\n182:   }\n183: \n184:   // Safe to proceed\n185:   avatar_element.src = user.profile.avatar.url;\n186:   console.log('[Avatar] Updated successfully');\n187: }\n188: \n189: // Modern JavaScript alternatives\n190: const avatar_url = user?.profile?.avatar?.url || '/default-avatar.png';\n191: const name = user.name ?? 'Anonymous';\n192: ```\n193: \n194: ### Complete Example: Contact Form with Multi-Layer Validation\n195: \n196: See [validation_patterns.js](../../assets/patterns/validation_patterns.js) for full implementation including:\n197: - Field-level validation (email, phone, required fields)\n198: - Real-time validation on blur\n199: - Form submission with sanitization\n200: - API error handling\n201: - XSS prevention\n202: \n203: ### Rules\n204: \n205: **ALWAYS:**\n206: - Validate function parameters (null/undefined/type checks)\n207: - Validate API responses before using data\n208: - Validate DOM elements exist before manipulating\n209: - Sanitize user input before storing or displaying\n210: - Provide fallback values for missing data\n211: - Use optional chaining (`?.`) for nested access\n212: - Add `try/catch` around risky operations\n213: - Log validation failures for debugging\n214: - Return early when validation fails\n215: \n216: **NEVER:**\n217: - Assume data exists without checking\n218: - Trust external data (APIs, user input, URL params)\n219: - Access nested properties without validation\n220: - Use innerHTML with unsanitized data\n221: - Ignore validation failures silently\n222: - Chain property access without null checks (`user.profile.avatar.url`)\n223: - Skip type checking function parameters\n224: \n225: **See also:** [validation_patterns.js](../../assets/patterns/validation_patterns.js) for production-ready validation templates\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ## 3. MINIFICATION & CDN DEPLOYMENT\n230: \n231: For JavaScript minification and CDN deployment workflows, see dedicated references:\n232: \n233: - **[minification_guide.md](../../deployment/minification_guide/overview_terser_and_patterns.md)** - Safe minification with terser, verification pipeline, debugging\n234: - **[cdn_deployment.md](../../deployment/cdn_deployment.md)** - Cloudflare R2 upload, version management, HTML updates\n235: \n236: ### Quick Workflow\n237: \n238: ```bash\n239: # 1. Make JS changes\n240: #    Edit: src/javascript/[folder]/[file].js\n241: \n242: # 2. Minify (output uses .min.js suffix in z_minified/)\n243: npx terser src/javascript/[folder]/[file].js --compress --mangle \\\n244:   -o src/javascript/z_minified/[folder]/[file].min.js\n245: \n246: # 3. Verify (AST check)\n247: node .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/assets/scripts/verify-minification.mjs\n248: \n249: # 4. Test (runtime check)\n250: node .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/assets/scripts/test-minified-runtime.mjs\n251: \n252: # 5. Update HTML versions\n253: #    Increment ?v=X.X.X in all referencing HTML files\n254: \n255: # 6. Upload to Cloudflare R2\n256: #    Dashboard → R2 → Upload minified file\n257: \n258: # 7. Verify live site\n259: #    Hard refresh, check console, test functionality\n260: ```\n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 329. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Defense-in-Depth Validation, Minification & CDN Deployment\ndescription: Three specialized workflows for writing robust frontend code with proper timing, validation, and cache management. — Defense-in-Depth Validation, Minification & CDN Deployment.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"defense in depth\"\n  - \"minification cdn deployment\"\n  - \"defense in patterns\"\n  - \"webflow defense in\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 3.5.0.10\n---\n\n# Defense-in-Depth Validation, Minification & CDN Deployment\n\nThree specialized workflows for writing robust frontend code with proper timing, validation, and cache management. — Defense-in-Depth Validation, Minification & CDN Deployment.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/implementation_workflows/validation_minification_and_cdn.md","text":"---\ntitle: Defense-in-Depth Validation, Minification & CDN Deployment\ndescription: Three specialized workflows for writing robust frontend code with proper timing, validation, and cache management. — Defense-in-Depth Validation, Minification & CDN Deployment.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"defense in depth\"\n  - \"minification cdn deployment\"\n  - \"defense in patterns\"\n  - \"webflow defense in\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 3.5.0.10\n---\n\n# Defense-in-Depth Validation, Minification & CDN Deployment\n\nThree specialized workflows for writing robust frontend code with proper timing, validation, and cache management. — Defense-in-Depth Validation, Minification & CDN Deployment.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nThree specialized workflows for writing robust frontend code with proper timing, validation, and cache management. — Defense-in-Depth Validation, Minification & CDN Deployment.\n\n### When to Use\n\nUse this reference when implementing or troubleshooting defense-in-depth validation, minification & cdn deployment.\n\n---\n\n## 2. DEFENSE-IN-DEPTH VALIDATION\n\n**When to use**: Form handling, API calls, DOM manipulation, user input, third-party data integration\n\n### Core Principle\n\nValidate at EVERY layer data passes through. Make bugs structurally impossible.\n\n### The Four Layers\n\n#### Layer 1: Entry Point Validation\n\nReject obviously invalid input at function boundary.\n\n```javascript\nfunction init_video(video_element, config) {\n  // Layer 1: Entry validation\n  if (!video_element) {\n    console.error('[Video] Element is required');\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  if (!(video_element instanceof HTMLVideoElement)) {\n    console.error('[Video] Must be HTMLVideoElement, got:', video_element);\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  if (!config || typeof config !== 'object') {\n    console.error('[Video] Config must be object, got:', config);\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  // Proceed with initialization...\n}\n```\n\n#### Layer 2: Processing Validation\n\nEnsure data makes sense for this operation.\n\n```javascript\nfunction update_video_source(video_element, new_source) {\n  // Layer 1: Entry validation\n  if (!video_element || !new_source) {\n    console.error('[Video] Missing required parameters');\n    return false;\n  }\n\n  // Layer 2: Processing validation\n  if (typeof new_source !== 'string' || new_source.trim() === '') {\n    console.error('[Video] Source must be non-empty string');\n    return false;\n  }\n\n  if (!new_source.match(/\\.(mp4|webm|m3u8)$/i)) {\n    console.error('[Video] Invalid video format:', new_source);\n    return false;\n  }\n\n  // Safe to proceed\n  video_element.src = new_source;\n  return true;\n}\n```\n\n#### Layer 3: Output Validation\n\nVerify results before using them.\n\n```javascript\nasync function fetch_user_data(user_id) {\n  // Layer 1: Entry validation\n  if (!user_id || typeof user_id !== 'string') {\n    throw new Error('Valid user_id required');\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const response = await fetch(`/api/users/${user_id}`);\n\n    // Layer 2: Response validation\n    if (!response.ok) {\n      throw new Error(`API error: ${response.status}`);\n    }\n\n    const data = await response.json();\n\n    // Layer 3: Output validation\n    if (!data || typeof data !== 'object') {\n      throw new Error('Invalid response data structure');\n    }\n\n    if (!data.name || !data.email) {\n      throw new Error('Required fields missing from response');\n    }\n\n    // Sanitize output before returning\n    return {\n      id: String(data.id),\n      name: String(data.name).trim(),\n      email: String(data.email).toLowerCase().trim(),\n      avatar: data.avatar || '/default-avatar.png'\n    };\n\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('[API] User fetch failed:', error);\n    // Return safe default\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### Layer 4: Safe Access Patterns\n\nPrevent crashes when accessing nested data.\n\n```javascript\n// ❌ DANGEROUS: No validation\nfunction display_user_avatar(user) {\n  const avatar = user.profile.avatar.url; // Crashes if any property null\n  document.querySelector('[avatar]').src = avatar;\n}\n\n// ✅ SAFE: Multiple layers of validation\nfunction display_user_avatar(user) {\n  // Layer 1: User object validation\n  if (!user || typeof user !== 'object') {\n    console.warn('[Avatar] Invalid user object');\n    show_default_avatar();\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Layer 2: Profile validation\n  if (!user.profile || typeof user.profile !== 'object') {\n    console.warn('[Avatar] User has no profile');\n    show_default_avatar();\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Layer 3: Avatar validation\n  if (!user.profile.avatar || !user.profile.avatar.url) {\n    console.warn('[Avatar] User has no avatar URL');\n    show_default_avatar();\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Layer 4: DOM element validation\n  const avatar_element = document.querySelector('[avatar]');\n  if (!avatar_element) {\n    console.error('[Avatar] Avatar element not found');\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Safe to proceed\n  avatar_element.src = user.profile.avatar.url;\n  console.log('[Avatar] Updated successfully');\n}\n\n// Modern JavaScript alternatives\nconst avatar_url = user?.profile?.avatar?.url || '/default-avatar.png';\nconst name = user.name ?? 'Anonymous';\n```\n\n### Complete Example: Contact Form with Multi-Layer Validation\n\nSee [validation_patterns.js](../../assets/patterns/validation_patterns.js) for full implementation including:\n- Field-level validation (email, phone, required fields)\n- Real-time validation on blur\n- Form submission with sanitization\n- API error handling\n- XSS prevention\n\n### Rules\n\n**ALWAYS:**\n- Validate function parameters (null/undefined/type checks)\n- Validate API responses before using data\n- Validate DOM elements exist before manipulating\n- Sanitize user input before storing or displaying\n- Provide fallback values for missing data\n- Use optional chaining (`?.`) for nested access\n- Add `try/catch` around risky operations\n- Log validation failures for debugging\n- Return early when validation fails\n\n**NEVER:**\n- Assume data exists without checking\n- Trust external data (APIs, user input, URL params)\n- Access nested properties without validation\n- Use innerHTML with unsanitized data\n- Ignore validation failures silently\n- Chain property access without null checks (`user.profile.avatar.url`)\n- Skip type checking function parameters\n\n**See also:** [validation_patterns.js](../../assets/patterns/validation_patterns.js) for production-ready validation templates\n\n---\n\n## 3. MINIFICATION & CDN DEPLOYMENT\n\nFor JavaScript minification and CDN deployment workflows, see dedicated references:\n\n- **[minification_guide.md](../../deployment/minification_guide/overview_terser_and_patterns.md)** - Safe minification with terser, verification pipeline, debugging\n- **[cdn_deployment.md](../../deployment/cdn_deployment.md)** - Cloudflare R2 upload, version management, HTML updates\n\n### Quick Workflow\n\n```bash\n# 1. Make JS changes\n#    Edit: src/javascript/[folder]/[file].js\n\n# 2. Minify (output uses .min.js suffix in z_minified/)\nnpx terser src/javascript/[folder]/[file].js --compress --mangle \\\n  -o src/javascript/z_minified/[folder]/[file].min.js\n\n# 3. Verify (AST check)\nnode .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/assets/scripts/verify-minification.mjs\n\n# 4. Test (runtime check)\nnode .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/assets/scripts/test-minified-runtime.mjs\n\n# 5. Update HTML versions\n#    Increment ?v=X.X.X in all referencing HTML files\n\n# 6. Upload to Cloudflare R2\n#    Dashboard → R2 → Upload minified file\n\n# 7. Verify live site\n#    Hard refresh, check console, test functionality\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":329,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/implementation_workflows/validation_minification_and_cdn.md","time":{"start":1783912467372,"end":1783912467385}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09bbfd2e8cf10090016a5458131a7081918d96107c9e0471f6"}},"id":"prt_f59780bab001yXinWVZ5QeluRL","sessionID":"ses_0a68bc60effeJzWL51JC6bkniv","messageID":"msg_f59777c8b001R4striWjqU0bS1"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783912467616,"sessionID":"ses_0a68bc60effeJzWL51JC6bkniv","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_W7uZskxpB6m1MBOhEdzXxwV3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"git status --short && git log --all --oneline --decorate -25 -- '.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment' '.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references' '.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets' '.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references' '.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/assets' '.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/assets'","timeout":120000,"workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public"},"output":"?? .opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/\n36bba13758 (HEAD -> skilled/v4.0.0.0, origin/wt/0033-benchmark-authoring, origin/skilled/v4.0.0.0, wt/0033-benchmark-authoring) docs(sk-doc): add alignment spec doc-sets for packets 017 and 019\n24b67450ca docs(sk-code): conform code-webflow assets — completes Request-1 split-doc alignment\ndd9e700477 docs(sk-code): conform code-webflow implementation split references (recursive)\nb541dab340 docs(sk-code): conform code-webflow js/shared refs + repair cross-surface ref links\ndc94ba0219 docs(sk-code): conform code-webflow debugging/deployment/performance/verification refs\nd39637b238 docs(sk-code): conform code-webflow animation/css/html references (recursive)\ndf72848de3 docs(sk-code): conform code-opencode assets to create-skill asset template\n38f06786b7 docs(sk-code): conform code-opencode shared split references (recursive)\n1922cffed7 docs(sk-code): conform code-opencode rust split references (recursive)\n3d79317657 docs(sk-code): conform code-opencode js/shell/typescript split references (recursive)\n6279a16bc1 docs(sk-code): conform code-opencode config/python single-file references + js direct\n2d24db2619 docs(sk-code): conform code-quality checklist assets to create-skill template\n885f2ca5c5 refactor(hooks): r